							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/tom-jenks/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/tom-jenks-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" alt="Tom Jenks" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/tom-jenks/">Tom Jenks</a></h6>
										Tom Jenks is the co-founder and editor of <em>Narrative Magazine</em>. He is a former editor of <em>Esquire</em>, <em>Gentlemen's Quarterly</em>, <em>The Paris Review</em>, and a senior editor at Scribners, where he edited Hemingway's <em>The Garden of Eden</em>. With Raymond Carver, he edited <em>American Short Story Masterpieces</em>. His writing has appeared in <em>Harper's</em>, <em>Ploughshares</em>, <em>Vanity Fair</em>, <em>Esquire</em>, <em>The American Scholar</em>, <em>Five Points</em>, the <em>Los Angeles Times</em>, and elsewhere. He has given classes at the Iowa Writers' Workshop, the Creative Writing Programs at University of California, and Washington University in St. Louis. He lives in San Francisco.																			</div>
								</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
							</div>
							<br class="clear"/>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div>
